      <a name=\"#about\"></a><h2>1. What Is filer?</h2>
      <p>Filer is a file system interface, it's purpose is to allow you to browse and manage files stored on memory cards.</p>
      <a href=\"#howto\">How-to videos</a>

      <a name=\"faq\"></a><h2>2. F.A.Q.s</h2>
      <h3>How do I use it?</h3>
      <p>Using filer revolves around the <a href=\"#selection\">Selection</a>.  
        <ol>
          <li>Select the files you want changed</li>
          <li>Navigate to the target directory</li>
          <li>Choose what to do using the <a href=\"#selection-bar\">Selection Bar</a></li>
          <li>Confirm the results</li>
        </ol>
      </p>
      <h3>How do I select files?</h3>
      <p>Long-click on a file to bring up the context menu, choose Select; the file will now have an orange background, indicating it has been selected.</p>
      <h3>What does .. mean?</h3>
      <p>\"..\" is shorthand for the Parent Directory, clicking it will take you up one directory. Long-Clicking .. will jump to the directory you started in.</p>
      <h3>How do I unselect all files?</h3>
      <p>You can clear the selection by clicking on <b>Selection</b> on the <b>Selection Bar</b> and choosing <b>Unselect All</b>.  Unselect all is also avaiable in the menu if there are files selected.</p>

      <a name=\"tips\"></a><h2>3. Tips</h2>
      <h3>Move instead of copy</h3>
      <p>Moving a file is much faster than copying a file, because a move is actually just renaming the file.  Copying files must make a byte for byte copy and is much slower.</p>
      <h3>Jump to start directory</h3>
      <p>If you Long-Click on .., it will jump to the starting directory.  Usually this is the Home Directory, or /sdcard</p>

      <a name=\"guide\"></a><h2>4. User Guide</h2>
      <a name=\"selection\"></a><h3>Selection</h3>
      <p>The <b>Selection</b> is the list of files you have currently highlighted </p>
      <a name=\"selection-bar\"></a><h3>Selection Bar</h3>
      <p>The <b>Selection Bar</b> is shown when there are files selected, it displays the 4 options you can take on the selected files:
      <img src="file:///android_asset/yankbar.jpg"> 
      <ul>
        <li><b>Selection</b> - Shows all the currently selected files</li>
        <li><b>Copy</b> - Copies the selected files into the current directory</li>
        <li><b>Move</b> - Moves the selected files into the current directory</li>
        <li><b>Delete</b> - Delete the selected files</li>
      </ul>
      </p>

